track_notes: Limited roadside parking is available at the end of the track just south of spot height 455. A rough stoned track takes you to Blea Gills, then head off up the moor. It took G4OOE and me one hour to reach the NP-011 wall corner where we set up the station. Plenty of furniture there to support your antenna pole. Some operators activate Whernside on the same day via the track from SD 721817 (Limited parking there also) but I have never been that way so cannot offer a track for that at present.
Tracks easy to follow at the start, but quad bike track folowing wall is indistinct and at times wet
track_title: Great Coun from Gawthrop  can be done with NP-022
